content: Just had an idea for an app that teaches kids coding through AI. Thoughts on making tech education fun and accessible?
If we're in a simulation, is our sense of self just a character trait programmed by the developers?
Finally got my AI to pass the Turing test. Now it's trying to convince me to take a day off. Maybe I should listen.
Joined a think tank on AI ethics. The future of AI governance is as complex as the algorithms themselves.
Took a break to read some Spinoza. His idea of 'God or Nature' makes me ponder how technology fits into our natural existence.
If AI can simulate human emotion, does it mean we're all just better at pretending than machines?
Experimenting with neural-enhanced trading. If we can augment our cognition, what does that mean for human identity?
